# Changed in v1.0.5
* Anagram search performance improvements: array-based letter matching, cached dictionaries, and suffix-sum pruning
* "Interesting words" now caps dominant first words at 10,000 and restarts, giving a broader view of results
* iOS share sheet now shows "Save to Photos" for GIF and video exports
* Re-enabled pause at start of animation
* Cleaned dictionaries: removed abbreviations, short non-words, and misplaced place names
* Added Google Play upload automation

# Changed in v1.0.3
* Enhanced guided tour: animated demo search, "Interesting words" step, and a seed favorite for new users
* Sync auth tokens now refresh automatically; extended token lifetime to 90 days
* Fixed sync loop caused by duplicate server client_ids from historical push bug
* Dictionary checkboxes now wrap on narrow screens so the Private edit button is always reachable

# Changed in v1.0.2
* Import a shared favorite directly into your collection — tap Import in the Favorites tab and paste a share link

# Changed in v1.0.1
* Drag to reorder anagrams in the multi-picker before animating — grab the ☰ handle and drag to set the sequence

# Changed in v1.0.0
* Sign in with Google or Apple (OAuth) — no password required
* Favorites list redesigned as a flat virtualized list for smooth scrolling with large collections
* Fixed sync reliability: server-side duplicate cleanup and tombstone TTL

# Changed in v0.9.8
* Sync edits now propagate across devices — editing a favorite on one device and syncing updates it on other devices
* Fixed in-app account deletion (now correctly removes all server data before deleting the account)
* Removed multi-input animation button from Favorites tab
* Added in-app Delete Account button in Sync settings

# Changed in v0.9.7
* Cross-device favorites sync via email sign-in (one-time passcode, no password)
* Share any favorite as a public link — copies URL to clipboard
* Fixed multiple sync reliability issues (server record bloat, duplicate tombstones, pull-evict loop)

# Changed in v0.9.6
* MP4 video export now captured at 24fps for smoother playback
* GIF export remains at 12fps (clean centisecond timing)

# Changed in v0.9.5
* Export animation as MP4 video (shareable to Instagram and other platforms that don't support GIF)
* Both "Save as GIF" and "Save as Video" share a single off-screen capture pass — second export is instant

# Changed in v0.9.4
* GIF export cached for the lifetime of the animation dialog — re-exporting skips re-render
* Capture initial frame before animation starts so GIF begins from the resting position
* GIF rendering now shows a progress bar

# Changed in v0.9.2
* Animation timing overhauled: single-driver per phase eliminates per-glyph stagger
* Animation text centered in display area
* Fixed iOS async layout timing for animation widget

# Changed in v0.9.0
* Animation export: save animation as GIF and share via platform share sheet
* Fixed GIF capture to use off-screen rendering with no race conditions
* Fixed iOS share sheet crash (UIKit calls dispatched to main thread)
* Fixed animation icon/badge positioning on iOS
* Upgraded to Fyne v2.7.0

# Changed in v0.8.0
* Multi-word place names now supported
* Animaiton will wrap itself up and stop gracefully after completing the sequence when tapped
* Multi input animations

# Changed in v0.7.0
* editor now animates changes 

# Changed in v0.6.0
* results for a given state are now cached

# Changed in v0.5.0
* when there aren't results, it now diplays "No Results" rather than just a blank list
* placeholder text on input fields
* detects and confirm addition of duplicate favorites
* significant speed improvement, especially with difficult inputs
* increased "interesting words" search limit to 100,000 rather than 50,000
* renamed references from "Main" tab to "Find" tab
* fixed bug with dictionary selection preservation
* fixed some of the display refresh logic
